KrisAssets to Purchase Mid Valley City Gardens Shares

-- B y   R y a n   W o o
-- 
2011-02-14T13:50:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/krisassets-to-purchase-mid-valley-city-gardens-shares-update1-.html
  KrisAssets Holdings Bhd ., the
Malaysian office and shopping mall operator, agreed to buy the
entire issued and paid-up ordinary share capital in Mid Valley
City Gardens Sdn. from IGB Corp.  KrisAssets will acquire 100,000 ordinary shares of 1
ringgit (33 cents) each in Mid Valley City Gardens, owner and
operator of The Gardens Mall in  Kuala Lumpur , according to a
filing to Bursa Malaysia today. The sale requires the approval
of KrisAssets and IGBâ€™s shareholders, the filing shows.  Trading in the shares of KrisAssets and IGB will resume on
Feb. 16. KrisAssets rose 0.5 percent to 3.90 ringgit on Feb. 11,
while IGB fell 1.3 percent to 2.32 ringgit.  Mid Valley City Gardens has an authorized share capital of
50 million ringgit comprising 5 million ordinary shares of 1
ringgit each and 900 million redeemable preference shares of
0.05 ringgit each, according to the filing. Of that, 100,000
shares and 250 million redeemable preference shares have been
issued and fully paid-up, the filing shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
